1.description_en: This little monster sports soft skin and a silly smile.

2.description_en: Giant lizards that hunt scouts for sport.

3.description_en: Peppery pals proficient at pulverizing passing perpetrators.

4.description_en: Their waggish expression belies their ferocity.

5.description_en: These barbarous bags may be smiling, but they're a sackful of trouble.

6.description_en: Small, agile creatures with contagious grins that fly through the darkness.

7.description_en: Small specters that delight in making young children cry.

8.description_en: This blob was born of a poisonous swamp and carries the same toxins in its body.

9.description_en: These creatures use their saw-like teeth to shred the bellies of their prey. Ouch!

10.description_en: Pig-like fish at home in both sea and sky.

11.description_en: Who knows what mischief these moles get up to with their spades...

12.description_en: Who knows what evil lurks in the hearts of men? These monsters do.

13.description_en: These slobbery monsters are renowned for their slippery skin.

14.description_en: As its name suggests, it likes to play with fire. However, it is not fond of the cold.

15.description_en: When surprised or threatened, these timid little fellows take refuge under their sturdy shells.

16.description_en: These creatures are born when bunches of vines gain sentience and take the form of dragons.

17.description_en: The poisonous tails of these predators can paralyze their prey at a pinch.

18.description_en: This hard-shelled crustacean boasts a nifty line in sidestepping.

19.description_en: The sight of one of these beasts dancing all by itself is strangely sorrowful.

20.description_en: These fiery creatures are actually passionate lovers as well as fighters.

21.description_en: Keep a close watch on these monsters - they can strike in the blink of an eye.

22.description_en: Once tall and proud, it now fights to avenge all the other trees cut down in their prime.

23.description_en: These sweet little creatures wave their tentacles about in the most adorable manner.

24.description_en: These lizards intimidate their enemies by unfurling their imposing neck frills.

25.description_en: Fowl faces that bode foul magic.

26.description_en: This monster's chilling exterior masks a rather cool and laid-back interior.

27.description_en: It's not the size of the hammer that counts. It's how you wield it.

28.description_en: Small, sentient suns circled by similar, somewhat smaller satellites.

29.description_en: Prickly denizens of the sea who see everything, you see.

30.description_en: Pestilent creatures that spawn in moist, dark places.

31.description_en: Slimologists have recently discovered that carnivorous slimes turn a reddish shade.

32.description_en: The horn of a nardragon can pierce any armour.

33.description_en: It's clear from the horn that you won't be brushing this hare aside in a hurry.

34.description_en: Foxy warriors whose skill with a foil is unsurpassed.

35.description_en: Decadent monsters whose love for worldly possessions keeps a smile on their faces.

36.description_en: Mischievous fiends who delight in blowing things up.

37.description_en: The souls of those who died in swamps...Always ready to give fellow monsters a hand!

38.description_en: These slimes count dragons amongst their relatives.

40.description_en: These sea dwellers know they're cute - and flaunt it!

41.description_en: These dirty dogs wrap their collars around their victims before landing the final blow.

42.description_en: This musician keeps his mic polished at all times, and is always ready to holler a tune.

43.description_en: The bodies of these wizards are highly resistant to the effects of magic.

44.description_en: Speedy savages whose sport is spiting slothful stragglers.

45.description_en: Malicious mummies who spread pestilence amongst the living.

46.description_en: These quirky slimes are more nimble than their heavy shells might have you believe.

47.description_en: These dragons keep a special brew in their jars especially for post-battle celebrations.

48.description_en: These felines are especially fond of their stripes.

49.description_en: Driven from their forest homes, they have turned on humans.

50.description_en: Few monsters can hold a light to these sparky fellows.

51.description_en: Two faces can be better than one, providing they can both breathe underwater.

52.description_en: Smelly boots inhabited by smellier sprites.

53.description_en: These unruly slimes slice their unsuspecting prey with swift slashes from their claws.

54.description_en: The tough scales of this dragon can only be pierced by exceptional blades.

55.description_en: Though still young cubs, their razor-sharp claws are already vicious weapons.

56.description_en: Wicked monsters who take the form of chests to lure adventurers in for the kill.

57.description_en: Unlike their cousins, these creatures dance for the good of their health.

58.description_en: Loath to relinquish life, this creature lives on though its flesh is long gone.

59.description_en: Once this vicious beast picks up the scent, its prey has little hope of escaping in one piece.

60.description_en: These rugged rocks smile through to the bitter end.

61.description_en: These demons give cutlery a bad name.

62.description_en: The dancing moves of these devils cannot be matched by any other monster.

63.description_en: Those felled by the blade often take it up in the afterlife.

65.description_en: Contrary to popular opinion, it is actually the slime giving the orders!

66.description_en: These practical fellows store food in their urns in case they get peckish during battle.

67.description_en: These slimes are astonishingly agile despite their heavy metal coating.

68.description_en: These insect assassins are skilled at skewering foes with their striking stingers.

69.description_en: Giant bat-like monsters that are most active during the hours of darkness.

71.description_en: These hyperactive hooligans often hyperbolise about how many heads they've hunted.

72.description_en: The buzz of their flapping wings is enough to unnerve anybody.

73.description_en: It is believed that these knights have sworn fealty to their beloved metal slimes.

74.description_en: Their powerful jaws confirm their place as rulers of the sea.

75.description_en: Evil eels with fearsome fangs to match their atrocious appetites.

76.description_en: These feline beasts have become possessed by the very men they ate.

77.description_en: Though typically mild-mannered, these monsters swing their hammers when angered.

78.description_en: Clockwork birds with an uncanny constitution.

79.description_en: Wicked demons created in the very heart of darkness to be a plague upon the world.

80.description_en: The risen remains of warriors felled in long forgotten wars.

81.description_en: Slimes who live virtuous lives are reincarnated in this saintly form.

82.description_en: These slimes have undergone a transformation brought about by contact with dark matter.

84.description_en: She-slimes exposed to dark matter become even more carnivorous!

85.description_en: Trying to tip these bovines over will earn you a kick in the rear.

86.description_en: Denizens of the forest who live in trees, targeting those who pass beneath the canopy.

87.description_en: Magical puppets brought to life for the sole purpose of dancing.

88.description_en: Mighty beasts kin to both lion and eagle.

89.description_en: These zombies serve as a warning to all would-be grave robbers.

90.description_en: Although they resemble drackies, they are actually allergic to blood!

91.description_en: With axe in hand, they are dedicated to chopping everything they find into tiny pieces.

92.description_en: Their fearsome appearance hides a surprisingly caring demeanor.

93.description_en: Winged warriors that track their targets from above before swooping in for the kill.

94.description_en: Though most at home in water, these sea creatures have also learnt to travel on land.

96.description_en: Deadly predators who use their amazing speed to shred their victims with lethal claws.

97.description_en: Play around with one of these and you're sure to get into trouble.

98.description_en: Powerful warriors of the sea that take pleasure in skewering their enemies.

99.description_en: This whopper is created from the cooperative power of a group of slimes merged into one.

100.description_en: The soul inside the armour searches for something it lost long ago.

102.description_en: Leopold's pack, tainted like him by darkness.

103.description_en: Masked marauders who hide their faces out of courtesy to beautiful monsters.

104.description_en: These medical specialists are more adept than their healslime cousins.

105.description_en: A fearsome, four-legged machine created to hunt metal monsters.

106.description_en: Smashing enemies into little bits brings a gleeful grin to their wicked faces.

107.description_en: Their liquid metal bodies soften even the most powerful impacts.

108.description_en: Chops bits off and they'll just grow back - truly a lumberjack's worst nightmare.

109.description_en: Masters of the blade who laugh in the face of Death. How rude.

110.description_en: He made the puppets all by himself.

111.description_en: They battle day and night, seeking to ascend to the throne of bug-kind.

112.description_en: It is said these man-made machines are imbued with the spirits of dragons.

113.description_en: Dark priests who have strayed far from the light.

114.description_en: As argon lizards grow older, their belies grow bolder.

115.description_en: The cloaks of these warriors are actually stained with grape juice.

116.description_en: One scratch from this skeleton's scythe may well earn you a free trip to the underworld.

118.description_en: Their mighty bodies can withstand even the pressure of the ocean depths.

119.description_en: A natural speedster, this beetle excels in body slams.

120.description_en: Knights who are slain astride their beloved steeds sometimes ride on into undeath.

121.description_en: Cocky fighters who are fearless in combat.

122.description_en: There is a rumour going around that he is boe's twin brother.

123.description_en: These deadly knights are stained in the blood of their victims.

124.description_en: Dark spirits born from the crews of ships that sink at sea.

125.description_en: These slimes have been tainted by the villainous knight who ride them.

126.description_en: Priests who have fallen and can't summon up the will to return to the light.

127.description_en: Serpents that reside in only the cleanest of waters.

128.description_en: Its penchant for spraying clouds of poisonous dust makes it a dangerous adversary.

129.description_en: Winged, silver monkeys with a slightly majestic air about them.

130.description_en: Experts at hurling their titanic bulk at enemies to devastating effect.

131.description_en: These cowardly monsters spend their whole lives hiding inside treasure boxes.

132.description_en: High-level demons whose expertise in explosive magic makes them feared by all.

133.description_en: Mad birds that are adept at wily maneuvering in combat.

134.description_en: These masters of healing cast Omniheal with the greatest of ease.

135.description_en: Greedy dragons who covet shiny objects and never forget a debt.

136.description_en: Primates who use their tremendous brute strength to swing a mighty club.

137.description_en: These bloodthirsty fiends pound their enemies into the ground, and the ground into dust.

138.description_en: These giants carry clubs carved from the trunks of even more gigantic trees.

139.description_en: Hardened goliaths possessing extraordinary power which they use to crush foes.

140.description_en: A mighty fiend whose training has made it twice the treat it once was.

141.description_en: Singers of the sea who synchronize their slap attack in symphony.

142.description_en: These alligators have evolved into flying beasts resistant to fire and ice.

143.description_en: These rugged ruffians are masters of both the martial and mental arts.

144.description_en: Bubble slimes figured out how to join together too, after watching normal slimes do their little trick.

145.description_en: The intimidating hairdos of these beasts will make your own hair stand on end.

146.description_en: The golden scales of this mighty dragon shield it from both frost and flame.

147.description_en: Shrimpy monsters who pack a wallop with their set of claws. Don't come the raw prawn with them!

148.description_en: Wild monsters that use their horns to toss their prey about before feasting.

149.description_en: The legendary king rules over all the monsters of the sea.

151.description_en: These slimes revere honour and chivalry above all else.

152.description_en: These lightning-fast warriors of the sea have made an art of surprising unwary mariners.

153.description_en: Elite soldiers of darkness who have mastered numerous weapons.

154.description_en: Men of the cloth who perform evil deeds are punished severely for their sins.

155.description_en: There is a nasty rumour going around that he is jum's twin brother.

156.description_en: Claims to be a natural-born leader and ingenious strategist.

157.description_en: This knight has dedicated himself to protecting one special person.

158.description_en: Gigantic birds of regal appearance feared throughout the skies.

159.description_en: Curls its arms and legs up into a ball to sleep at night - how cute!

160.description_en: Demonic creatures who excel at both physical and magical combat.

161.description_en: These sadistic aristocrats continue to oppress the masses even in death.

162.description_en: Love of gold has turned these miserly machines into their favorite colour.

163.description_en: This fiendish creature has dyed its fur a terrifying shade of pink!

164.description_en: These monarchs move with menacing speed that is never hampered by their protoplasm.

165.description_en: Some believe these dragons were turned black by the blistering heat of their own breath.

166.description_en: A natural speedster, this beetle excels in body slams.

167.description_en: Once opposed a certain trio of warriors while in the service of Hargon.

168.description_en: Few who fall upon this ingenious trap ever live to tell the tale.

169.description_en: An infamous bandit who steals from the rich and gives to no one.

170.description_en: Fearsome warriors who have lost their heading and their heads!

171.description_en: The gigantic arms of this burly dragon are registered as lethal weapons.

172.description_en: This killing machine of the sea is armed with long and deadly tentacles.

173.description_en: An amateur musician whose enthusiasm far, far, FAR exceeds his musical talent.

174.description_en: These mechanical monstrosities were manufactured to menace all mankind.

175.description_en: During the daytime, these beasts practice their clubbing techniques on small animals.

176.description_en: The lost soul of a king who terrorized his people and ruined the kingdom.

177.description_en: Although made of darkonium, they won't get a scout into the finals of the challenge.

178.description_en: This regal deity is known as the Zenith dragon on another plane of existence.

179.description_en: Likes to play puppet shows with its tentacles at passing ships.

180.description_en: This great ruler is worshipped as a god by many monsters.

181.description_en: This creature is walking proof that the whole can be greater than the sum of its parts.

182.description_en: A god of destruction who plans to usher death unto all living beings.

183.description_en: A powerful pirate who perished pursuing a line of light leading to legendary lands.
183.location: Defeat Captain Crow in Pirate side quest

184.description_en: These sagely slimes are privy to arcane knowledge, and even the secret of the ooze.

185.description_en: The final form of a jester who yearned for the forbidden power of a scepter.

186.description_en: This monarch spoken of in ancient lore was once bested by the legendary dragon warrior.

187.description_en: A malevolent beast born of the remnants of an ancient castle.

188.description_en: The vast powers wielded by this dark lord strike fear into even spirits of darkness.

190.description_en: This chaotic canine appears to be empowered - or is it controlled? - by the sceptre.
190.location: Collect all of the skills in your library

191.description_en: These multi-faceted slimes are strong against any manner of attack.

192.description_en: A lord of the underworld from before recorded history.
192.location: Defeat the Estark after getting the brass key.

193.description_en: A monstrous king whose ambitions extend even unto the world of dreams.

194.description_en: In ages past, he sought to become a god.

195.description_en: This holy bird soars between worlds, protecting them from the darkness.
195.location: Collect all of the monsters in your library

196.description_en: A mighty god of darkness who comes in a very small package.

198.description_en: He never did get along well with the other children in school.

199.description_en: The Lord of the Dragovians, having discarded his human form.

200.description_en: My word! Where am I? And just where is my precious Medea!?

201.description_en: A being suffused with holy energy whose existence is shrouded in mystery.

202.description_en: A divine bird who can command the element of fire.

204.description_en: A divine lizard who can command the element of water.

205.description_en: Its holy mission is to seal the entrance to the dark world using the power of the Mark.

206.description_en: A mighty bird whose wings beast with the force of a firestorm.

207.description_en: A mighty ape whose hide is tougher than an earthen fortress wall.

208.description_en: A mighty dragon whose vault of knowledge and lore is deeper than all the seas.

210.description_en: The final form of the Incarnus, empowered by the magic of the Mark.
